cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques to classify different types of assertions about activity performance in clinical free text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses SVM and CNN models, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with healthcare-related data, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
